article_title: Japan’s Top Male Gymnast Fails Qualifying Event
meta_description:
Kohei Uchimura, Japan’s top male gymnast, looking to end his long career in glory, instead slipped and fell Saturday during his high bar qualifying event.  Known for winning all-around gymnastic championships for years, the 32-year-old athlete was looking to compete only in the high bar this year, but his fall leaves him out of the competition.  

Tropical Storm Nepartak is headed for Japan, bringing the threat of heavy rains and strong winds.

meta_description: WASHINGTON (SBG) — Six senior-level employees at one of New Jersey's largest health care systems were fired for refusing to get vaccinated against COVID-19,RWJBarnabas Health confirmed to Sinclair in a statement.  RWJBarnabas Health, which runs 11 acute-care hospitals in the state, has a policy set in May that all employees at the supervisor level or above must be vaccinated against the virus.
